                "relevance": "A roughly contemporary messianic expectation involving "
                             "a messianic judge. The Parables' Elect One combines this "
                             "Davidic royal judgment with the Danielic heavenly Son of Man.",
                "canon": False
            }
        ],

        "cross_refs": [
            {"ref": "Matthew 25:31", "note": "'When the Son of Man comes in his glory and sits on his glorious throne' — the direct NT echo of 1 Enoch 45:3's enthronement language", "type": "nt"},
            {"ref": "Matthew 10:32-33", "note": "'Everyone who acknowledges me before others, I also will acknowledge... whoever denies me, I also will deny' — the acknowledgment/denial criterion matches 1 Enoch 45's judgment standard", "type": "nt"},
            {"ref": "2 Peter 3:13", "note": "'New heavens and a new earth in which righteousness dwells' — the cosmic transformation that 1 Enoch 45:4-5 anticipates", "type": "nt"},
            {"ref": "Revelation 21:1", "note": "'A new heaven and a new earth, for the first heaven and the first earth had passed away' — the transformed cosmos that 1 Enoch 45 envisions", "type": "nt"},
            {"ref": "Isaiah 65:17", "note": "'I am about to create new heavens and a new earth' — the OT source for the cosmic renewal theme", "type": "ot"}
