                        "tegbaromu), meaning actions and their consequences, not "
                        "merely beliefs. This parallels Matthew 25:35-40 where the "
                        "Son of Man judges based on concrete deeds of mercy. Verses "
                        "4-5 then describe cosmic transformation: heaven and earth "
                        "will be changed on the day of the Elect One's judgment. "
                        "This is not merely political regime change but a renewal "
                        "of the entire created order — the 'new heavens and new "
                        "earth' of Isaiah 65:17 and Revelation 21:1. The Parables "
                        "integrate individual judgment (works tried) with cosmic "
                        "renewal (heaven and earth transformed), exactly as the "
                        "NT does in Romans 8:19-23 and Revelation 20-21."
            }
        ]
