                               "One exercises the council's judicial function — sorting "
                               "all the dead at the resurrection.",

        "sections": [
            {
                "heading": "The Threefold Giving Back (51:1)",
                "body": "Earth, Sheol, and hell each 'give back' their dead. The "
                        "threefold formula emphasizes totality. The language of "
                        "'entrusting' and 'giving back' treats death as temporary "
                        "custody, not a final state. This directly parallels "
                        "Revelation 20:13."
            },
            {
                "heading": "The Elect One's Sorting (51:2-5)",
                "body": "The Elect One 'shall choose the righteous and holy from "
                        "among them.' He who was chosen now chooses. The result: "
                        "'the righteous shall dwell upon the earth, and the elect "
                        "shall walk thereon' (51:5) — inheritance of a transformed "
                        "earth, not escape from it."
