        "era": "parables",
        "type": "chapter",

        "synopsis": "Angels stir up the Parthians and Medes to invade 'the land of "
                    "the elect.' The invaders are swallowed up. This chapter is the "
                    "key dating criterion for the Parables, as the Parthian imagery "
                    "most likely refers to the invasion of 40 BC.",

        "key_verse": {
            "ref": "1 Enoch 56:5-7",
            "text": "And in those days the angels shall return and hurl themselves "
