                "heading": "Blessedness of the Righteous (58:1-6)",
                "body": "The opening of the third Parable shifts to positive vision: "
                        "the eternal blessedness of the righteous. The 'light of the "
                        "sun' and 'light of eternal life' represent two grades of "
                        "glory — natural and supernatural. The righteous transcend "
                        "created light into the uncreated light of God's own "
                        "presence. This tradition develops through John 1:4 ('in "
                        "him was life, and the life was the light of all people') "
                        "and Revelation 21:23 ('the glory of God is its light')."
            }
        ]
