                        "as 'son of man' over 90 times, emphasizing mortal humanity "
                        "before divine presence. Daniel 7:13 transforms this ordinary "
                        "phrase: 'one like a son of man' comes 'with the clouds of "
                        "heaven' — transport elsewhere reserved for deity (Psalm "
                        "104:3, Isaiah 19:1) — and receives 'dominion and glory and "
                        "a kingdom.' The identity in Daniel is debated: Collins and "
