                        "of Man was a Jewish concept before Jesus. If post-Christian, "
                        "they might reflect Christian influence. Milik's proposal of "
                        "a 3rd century AD date is now almost universally rejected. "
                        "The Parables contain no distinctively Christian elements: no "
                        "crucifixion, no resurrection of the Son of Man, no incarnation, "
                        "no Gentile mission, no church. The consensus among specialists "
                        "(Nickelsburg, VanderKam, Boccaccini, Charlesworth) dates the "
                        "Parables to the late 1st century BC or early 1st century AD "
